---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
---
<BaseLayout title="Changelog — YieldRadar" description="YieldRadar changelog — latest features, improvements, and bug fixes across all versions.">

<section style="padding: 3rem 0 1rem;">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h1>Changelog</h1>
    <p class="lead">Release history for YieldRadar — what shipped, what changed, and what was fixed.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-inner">
  <div class="changelog-entry">
    <div class="changelog-header">
      <span class="changelog-version">v1.2</span>
      <span class="changelog-date">April 2026</span>
      <span class="changelog-badge">Latest</span>
    </div>
    <div class="changelog-body">
      <h3>Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>4 new chains — Optimism, Avalanche, Hyperliquid L1, Sui (total: 10 chains, covering 85%+ DeFi TVL)</li>
        <li>Alert deduplication with persistent tracking — no more duplicate notifications for the same pool within a scan cycle</li>
        <li>Minimum APY filter — set a floor to only receive alerts above your target yield</li>
        <li>Data export — export your alert history and pool data for personal analysis</li>
        <li>GoPlus expanded to 5 security endpoints — token, address, rugpull, approval, and phishing site detection</li>
        <li>Emission decay detection — flags pools with unsustainable reward structures</li>
        <li>Simplified onboarding — reduced from 5 steps to 3 for faster setup</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Improvements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>GoPlus authentication flow rewritten for reliability — fewer failed security checks during high-load periods</li>
        <li>Pipeline fetch hang fix — resolved timeout issues in DeFiLlama data pulls</li>
        <li>API audit fixes across the data pipeline — improved error handling and retry logic</li>
        <li>Alert message formatting improvements with inline action buttons</li>
        <li>Test suite expanded from 504 to 740 tests</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="changelog-entry">
    <div class="changelog-header">
      <span class="changelog-version">v1.1</span>
      <span class="changelog-date">April 2026</span>
    </div>
    <div class="changelog-body">
      <h3>Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Normalized 0–100 risk scoring with four-tier classification (Safe, Watch, Speculative, Danger)</li>
        <li>GoPlus Security API integration — automated honeypot detection, malicious contract scanning, and token tax analysis</li>
        <li>DeFiLlama protocol metadata enrichment — TVL, audit status, and protocol age factor into risk scores</li>
        <li>APY historical snapshots with 7-day and 30-day trend analytics</li>
        <li>Telegram Stars subscription payments — pay for Pro directly in Telegram</li>
        <li>Launch pricing: Pro tier at $9.99/mo, locked in permanently for early adopters</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Improvements</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Deep-dive command with yield breakdown, risk factor analysis, and similar pool suggestions</li>
        <li>Daily digest with top 3 opportunities, rising APY alerts, and yield warnings</li>
        <li>Settings flow for chain preferences, risk tolerance, and alert frequency</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="changelog-entry">
    <div class="changelog-header">
      <span class="changelog-version">v1.0</span>
      <span class="changelog-date">March 2026</span>
    </div>
    <div class="changelog-body">
      <h3>Features</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>Data pipeline with 5-minute polling from DeFiLlama (started with 6 chains, now 10)</li>
        <li>Multi-factor risk scoring engine with 10 weighted factors per pool</li>
        <li>Telegram bot with onboarding flow, real-time alerts, daily digest, deep-dive analysis, and settings</li>
        <li>User management with freemium tiers (Free: 10 alerts/day, Pro: unlimited)</li>
        <li>Docker deployment with multi-stage build and health monitoring</li>
      </ul>
      <h3>Infrastructure</h3>
      <ul>
        <li>SQLite (better-sqlite3, WAL mode) for persistent storage</li>
        <li>Grammy bot framework with conversations plugin</li>
        <li>Node.js 24 with TypeScript (ESM, strict mode)</li>
        <li>Vitest test suite (740 tests)</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .changelog-entry {
    border: 1px solid var(--color-border);
    border-radius: 12px;
    padding: 2rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    background: var(--color-card);
  }
  .changelog-header {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    flex-wrap: wrap;
  }
  .changelog-version {
    font-family: 'Space Grotesk', sans-serif;
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--color-primary);
  }
  .changelog-date {
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, var(--color-text));
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
  .changelog-badge {
    background: var(--color-primary);
    color: #fff;
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    padding: 0.2rem 0.6rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
  }
  .changelog-body h3 {
    font-size: 0.95rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 1rem 0 0.5rem 0;
    color: var(--color-text);
  }
  .changelog-body h3:first-child {
    margin-top: 0;
  }
  .changelog-body ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.2rem;
  }
  .changelog-body li {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    margin-bottom: 0.4rem;
    color: var(--color-text-secondary, var(--color-text));
  }
</style>
